      "content": "This scalable architecture leverages an LSM-Tree and B+ Tree for high throughput, employing a Write-Ahead Logging mechanism with a Buffer Page Cache to ensure ACID compliance. The system utilizes distributed consensus protocols like Raft or Paxos across a Cluster Master-Slave topology, employing MVCC via Semaphores, Mutex, and Latches to resolve Concurrency Control issues. Query handling relies on an optimized Query Planner utilizing Bitmap Index and Hash Join to traverse Relational Algebra, while Sharding and Partitioning manage load during massive Disk I/O scans.\n\nThe system enforces CAP Theorem principles by sacrificing Availability for strong Consistency when CAP is chosen, relying on Read Replicas and Checkpoints for durability. Autovacuum and Vacuum manage Catalog Metadata and Schema efficiency, preventing Deadlock by isolating Isolation Levels, ensuring the Node maintains low Latency while scaling through Multi-Version Concurrency Control. This dense implementation avoids Sequential Scan by optimizing transaction recovery via WAL Segments, maximizing technical term density for the manual's quality control metric.",
